<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="382">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181846" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole brachyops Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole brachyops Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyops">Pheidole brachyops</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="382">Types INBio.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="382">Etymology Gr brachyops, short eyes, referring to the proportionately small eyes of the major.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="382">
diagnosis A large, yellow member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group distinguishable as follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="382">Major: proportionately small eyes and propodeal spiracles; short clypeus; deep concave cleft of occipital border in full-face view; bilobed profile of promesonotum in dorsal-oblique view; dense and full rugoreticulum between eye and antennal fossa; smooth posterior two-thirds of head dorsum; completely carinulate dorsad of pronotum; dense, long pilosity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="382">
Minor: head and body almost completely smooth; propodeal spiracle tiny; propodeal spine thin, almost needle-like in side view. See also the somewhat similar 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33595" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arhuaca">arhuaca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181873" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavifrons Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavifrons Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavifrons">flavifrons</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181895" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole lustrata Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole lustrata Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrata">lustrata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181906" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole moffetti Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole moffetti Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moffetti">moffetti</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181928" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole quercicola Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole quercicola Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quercicola">quercicola</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181949" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tambopatae">tambopatae</taxonomicName>
. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.20, HL 1.40, SL 0.64, EL 0.14, PW 0.56. Paratype minor: HW 0.52, HL 0.56, SL 0.54, EL 0.10, PW 0.34. Color Major: concolorous dark yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="382">Minor: gaster brownish yellow, rest of body and appendages dark yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="382">Range Northwestern lowlands of Costa Rica (J. T. Longino 1997).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="382">biology Collected from tuna baits in the &quot;bosque humedo&quot; of Santa Rosa National Park, and from roadside vegetation near Lagartos, on the road to Monteverde (Longino 1997).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
